On Mon, Jun 28, 1999 at 04:18:35PM -0400, Igor Schein wrote:
> Hi,
> 
> my 1st posting on this list - please forgive
> if I violate any of the unwritten rules of the list.
> 
> Here's the setup.  Solaris 2.5 machine as NFS server,
> Linux 2.2.5 machine as NFS client.  When compiling
> something on Linux machine, some output files get corrupted.
> The above is the only server-client combination for which
> data corruption is observed.
> 
> Thanks 
> 
> Igor
> 
	I had to add to following lines in the /etc/system file on
	the Solaris machine :
*
*       Patch applique le 15/01/1999 pour contournement du probleme
*       de fichiers corrompus avec les clients Linux en noyau 2.2.x
*       Voir le bug 4071076 dans SunSolve
*
        set nfssrv:rfs_write_async=0
A+,
